famous.description: For sale is a Pleyel Model P 131, SN #262710 purchased new 2006. Piano has been scrumptiously maintained. Has had light use. Hammers are in terrific condition. Cabinet is unmarred. Tuning pins are tight. String wire is shiny. Has been kept in a very stable environment with proper humidity.This instrument may have an obscure brand, but the company has had a rich history as a piano of choice to Chopin, Debussy, Saint-Saëns, Ravel, de Falla and Stravinsky. Many famous piano instructors also chose Pleyel – read about in the Wikipedia. Pleyels rise above the other mass-produced pianos like Yamaha, Kawai and Petrof. They are more comparable to Schimmel. As they are not produced in great volume, the construction is more crafted. If you read the piano forums, folks tend to come back and purchase the Pleyel. They really do stand out above others.•	Consistent quality•	Sweet sound and powerful bass section•	Excellent dynamic abilities and possesses a sostenuto pedal! This indicates the type musician the designers         had in mind for this instrument: accomplished.•	Renner action including hammers special to this piano•	Action touch is slightly lighter than average•	Very robust frame (piano weighs over 600 lbs)•	Gorgeous wood graining and finish. Top notch.Recommend you play the Kawai, Yamaha, etc. first and then try this instrument. It is likely your last stop! There are extremely few that are being sold used. Most musicians keep them once acquired.
